# Environment variables for Butlers AI agent framework
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CREDENTIALS APPROACH
#
#   All runtime secrets (API keys, Telegram tokens, email passwords,
#   Google OAuth, etc.) are stored in each butler's PostgreSQL database
#   and managed via the dashboard Secrets page:
#
#     https://<your-host>/butlers/secrets
#
#   Environment variables below are ONLY for infrastructure bootstrap
#   (database connection, observability). You do NOT need to set API
#   keys or integration credentials here.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Optional: PostgreSQL connection (defaults shown)
# POSTGRES_HOST=localhost
# POSTGRES_PORT=5432
# POSTGRES_USER=butlers
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=your-db-password
# POSTGRES_DB=butlers

# Optional: OpenTelemetry exporter endpoint for tracing
# OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:4318

# Optional: Google OAuth app credentials (bootstrap only — seeds the
# initial OAuth flow via the dashboard. After bootstrap, stored in DB.)
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=your-oauth-client-id
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=your-oauth-client-secret
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:40200/api/oauth/google/callback

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NETWORK SECURITY (Docker Compose)
#
#   The egress firewall (scripts/egress-firewall.sh) blocks containers
#   from reaching private subnets (LAN, Tailscale) while allowing
#   public internet. To grant access to specific tailnet services,
#   list their Tailscale IPs here.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Space-separated Tailscale IPs that containers may reach.
# Common services: OTEL collector, Garage (S3), external Postgres.
# Find IPs with: tailscale status
# ALLOWED_TAILNET_HOSTS=100.x.x.x 100.y.y.y 100.z.z.z
